You will next be prompted for the offset to the first column to be
processed, <off>.  If you don't specify an offset, the default will
be 1.

$input
$if answer=''
  $cmd setl off 1
$else
  $cmd setl off &ANSWER

You will next be prompted for the length of each column to be
processed, <len>.  If you don't specify a length, the default will
be 32767.

$input
$if answer=''
  $cmd setl len 32767
$else
  $cmd setl len &ANSWER

You will next be prompted for the number of columns to be processed
in each line, <ncols>.  If you don't specify a number of columns,
the default will be 1.

enter <ncols> or null for default = 1
$input
$if answer=''
  $cmd setl ncols 1
$else
  $cmd setl ncols &ANSWER
